race.comment: Over to the Cup and Waller's progressive former import GOD'S WINDOW (11) looks set to peak. He's a lightly raced 5yo gelding who had shown good ability in some strong races in England before coming out here off a long spell this time in. He got to 2000m last time and showed plenty of improvement, now dropping 5.5kg up to 2400m which will suit much better. QUIETNESS (6) was only second up in the G3 Coongy Cup and ran very well as a $4 chance, perhaps not ridden ideally when ridden back from a wide draw. She's out wide again here but surely rolls forward this time and should give a sight. ARAPAHO (1) has to give them all weight as a dual G1 winner. His run two back in the G3 Kingston Town with 58kg is good form for this. SAYEDATY SADATY (4) was too close to a very strong pace last time and can bounce back here. INTERPRETATION (3) struggled in the same race but had been solid prior and did win this last year, albeit off a better lead up run.
